Part 1 : Node.js HTTP Server (Core Modules Only)

Create an HTTP server only Node.js core modules (no Express, no npm packages). The server must run on port 3000 and support the following routes:

- GET /updateUser Append a new visitor entry with the current timestamp to visitors.log.
- GET /savelog Read and return the full contents of visitors.log.
- POST /backup Copy the contents of visitors.log into a new file called backup.log.
- GET /clearlog Clear the contents of visitors.log.
- GET /serverinfo Return system information in JSON format.
